his%20nose.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWhile%20nose%20breathing%20can%20benefit%20sleep%2C%20experts%20have%20cautioned%20against%20mouth%20taping.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fjimmy-fallon%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJimmy%20Fallon%3C%2Fa%3E%20approaches%20his%2050th%20birthday%2C%20he%20has%20no%20interest%20in%20throwing%20a%20big%20party.%20Instead%2C%20he'd%20rather%20have%20a%20good%20night's%20sleep.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20been%20taking%20better%20care%20of%20myself.%20I'm%20reading%20a%20lot%20about%20breathing%20more%20through%20my%20nose.%20I%20swear!%20It's%20much%20better%20for%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20an%20interview%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.parents.com%2Ftake-five-with-grace-jimmy-fallon-8702306%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EParents%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20guess%20people%20that%20talk%20a%20lot%20breathe%20through%20their%20mouths%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Fallon%2C%20who%20has%20hosted%20%26quot%3BThe%20Tonight%20Show%26quot%3B%20for%20a%20decade.%20He%20added%20that%20he%20was%20reading%20a%20book%20on%20taping%20his%20mouth%20shut%20to%20force%20himself%20to%20breathe%20through%20his%20nose%20%E2%80%94%20in%20hopes%20of%20getting%20a%20better%20night's%20sleep.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20to%20do%20this%20under%20supervision%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BSo%2C%20I'm%20going%20to%20have%20security%20guards%20next%20to%20my%20bed%20and%20try%20this%20%E2%80%94%20I'm%20not%20kidding!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20June%2C%20Fallon%20talked%20about%20sleep%20and%20breathing%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fandrew-huberman-swears-by-morning-sunlight-healthy-circadian-clock-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAndrew%20Huberman%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20neuroscientist%20at%20Stanford%20University%20and%20the%20host%20of%20the%20%26quot%3BHuberman%20Lab%26quot%3B%20podcast.%20%26quot%3BIf%20I%20could%20invest%20money%2C%20I%20would%20invest%20in%20breathing%2C%26quot%3B%20Fallon%20told%20Huberman%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DpE8TH8hZ-48%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Tonight%20Show.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStudies%20have%20found%20that%20nose%20breathing%20can%20indeed%20benefit%20health.%20A%202023%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.physiology.org%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1152%2Fajpregu.00148.2023%3Futm_source%3DAJPRegu%26utm_medium%3DPressRelease%26utm_campaign%3D1.17.2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20in%20the%20American%20Journal%20of%20Physiology%20found%20that%20nose%20breathing%20can%20lower%20blood%20pressure%20and%20reduce%20risk%20factors%20for%20heart%20disease.%20In%20addition%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F7939149%2F%23full-view-affiliation-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Goteborg%20found%20that%20nasal%20breathing%20can%20decrease%20snoring%20and%20alleviate%20sleep%20apnea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20TikTok%2C%20users%20have%20turned%20to%20mouth%20tapes%20to%20seal%20their%20mouths%20shut%20to%20promote%20nose%20breathing.%20At%20the%20time%20of%20writing%2C%20there%20are%20more%20than%2011%2C200%20posts%20under%20the%20hashtag%20%23mouthtape.%20Users%20who%20have%20tried%20mouth%20taping%20said%20it%20leads%20to%20deeper%20sleep%2C%20better%20oral%20hygiene%2C%20and%20reduced%20snoring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20no%20conclusive%20research%20proves%20these%20purported%20benefits%20of%20mouth%20taping%2C%20and%20experts%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmouth-taping-for-sleep-oral-health-doctors-warn-of-risks-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecautioned%20against%20the%20trend%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%