s%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-blocked-supreme-court-strikes-down-debt-cancellation-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estruck%20down%20Biden's%20first%20attempt%20at%20broad%20debt%20relief%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Expected%20to%20benefit%20over%2030%20million%20borrowers%2C%20the%20plan%20would%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loans-debt-forgiveness-who-qualifies-borrowers-relief-education-department-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecancel%20some%20or%20all%20student%20debt%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20borrowers%20with%20unpaid%20interest%2C%20those%20who%20have%20been%20in%20repayment%20for%20at%20least%2020%20years%2C%20and%20those%20who%20attended%20schools%20that%20left%20them%20with%20too%20much%20debt%20compared%20to%20post-graduation%20earnings%2C%20among%20other%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20final%20rule%20for%20the%20relief%20has%20yet%20to%20be%20published%2C%20and%20the%20Education%20Department%20previously%20announced%20it%20planned%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-biden-second-attempt-october-timeline-debt-relief-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebegin%20implementing%20the%20relief%20in%20October%3C%2Fa%3E.%20However%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fago.mo.gov%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F1-Complaint-Student-Loans.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elawsuit%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20that%20the%20department%20had%20been%20working%20on%20the%20plan's%20implementation%20prior%20to%20publishing%20the%20final%20rule%2C%20according%20to%20internal%20documents%20they%20obtained%20from%20the%20department%20to%20servicers%2C%20and%20called%20for%20the%20court%20to%20put%20a%20stop%20to%20the%20relief%20pending%20a%20final%20legal%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNot%20only%20is%20this%20attempt%20the%20Secretary's%20most%20aggressive%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20lawsuit%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20also%20the%20weakest%20one%20yet.%20The%20Secretary%20has%20already%20failed%20to%20mass%20cancel%20student%20loans%20with%20the%20two%20statutes%20he%20thought%20were%20more%20plausible.%20It%20is%20thus%20unsurprising%20that%20this%20third%20plan%20rests%20on%20the%20least%20plausible%20textual%20authority%20yet.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20GOP-led%20states%20said%20that%20the%20department%20was%20planning%20to%20enact%20the%20relief%20as%20early%20as%20September.%20According%20to%20the%20internal%20documents%20the%20states%20obtained%20attached%20alongside%20the%20lawsuit%2C%20the%20Education%20Department%20sent%20a%20memo%20to%20servicer%20MOHELA%20stating%20that%20%26quot%3Bin%20September%20of%202024%2C%20the%20Biden-Harris%20Administration%20will%20launch%20the%20Federal%20Student%20Loan%20Debt%20Initiative.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20documents%20do%20not%20indicate%20which%20specific%20parts%20of%20the%20relief%2C%20if%20any%2C%20would%20have%20been%20implemented%20in%20September%2C%20but%20the%20lawsuit%20argued%20that%20the%20department%20was%20not%20adhering%20to%20the%20regulatory%20process%20by%20making%20plans%20to%20get%20the%20relief%20to%20borrowers%20prior%20to%20the%20final%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Education%20Department%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider%20on%20this%20latest%20lawsuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20states%20also%20argued%20that%20the%20relief%20would%20harm%20student-loan%20company%20MOHELA%2C%20which%20is%20based%20in%20Missouri%2C%20one%20of%20the%20states%20leading%20the%20lawsuit.%20They%20said%20that%20MOHELA%2C%20would%20lose%20revenue%20through%20forgiven%20loans%2C%20and%20the%20plan%20would%20increase%20administrative%20costs%20for%20the%20servicer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Education%20Department%20has%20not%20yet%20commented%20on%20how%20this%20will%20impact%20its%20plans%20for%20broad%20relief.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20Biden's%20new%20SAVE%20income-driven%20repayment%20plan%20is%20blocked%20in%20court%20following%20a%20lawsuit%20from%20a%20group%20of%20GOP%20state%20attorneys%20general%20who%20sued%20to%20block%20cheaper%20payments%20and%20debt%20cancellation%2C%20with%20over%208%20million%20enrolled%20borrowers%20waiting%20in%20limbo%20pending%20a%20final%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-borrowers-first-lawsuit-broad-debt-cancellation-biden-relief-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725398143000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a945b3fb6d32635ee5105d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-borrowers-first-lawsuit-broad-debt-cancellation-biden-relief-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Seven%20GOP-led%20states%20have%20filed%20the%20first%20lawsuit%20targeting%20Biden's%20upcoming%20plan%20to%20cancel%20student%20debt%20for%20millions%20of%20borrowers.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22asheffey%40businessinsider.com%20(Ayelet%20Sheffey)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A232%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-borrowers-first-lawsuit-broad-debt-cancellation-biden-relief-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20US%20Air%20Force's%20potential%20shift%20to%20adaptable%20'light%20fighters'%20to%20solve%20budget%20woes%20is%20more%20complicated%20than%20it%20seems%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22990%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20render%20of%20an%20F-35%20equipped%20with%20Mako%20missiles.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a3c812a0fc5856d597bfc6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22556%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20render%20of%20an%20F-35%20equipped%20with%20Mako%20missiles.%3Cp%3ELockheed%20Martin%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20US%20Air%20Force%20may%20shift%20its%20focus%20from%20costly%20next-gen%20jets%20to%20cheaper%2C%20adaptable%20light%20fighters.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20USAF%20chief%20proposed%20pursuing%20modular%20designs%20for%20its%20fleet%20instead%20of%20long-term%20survivability.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20%26quot%3Bbuilt%20to%20adapt%26quot%3B%20approach%20could%20cut%20costs%20and%20meet%20emerging%20challenges%20on%20the%20battlefield.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20senior%20Air%20Force%20officials%20are%20now%20pointing%20toward%20a%20dramatic%20shift%20in%20America's%20next%20stealth%20fighter%20program%2C%20with%20high-cost%20and%20high-capability%20platforms%20like%20the%20Next%20Generation%20Air%20Dominance%20(NGAD)%20fighter%20in%20development%20potentially%20shelved%20in%20favor%20of%20smaller%2C%20lighter%2C%20and%20cheaper%20aircraft%20built%20to%20adapt%20to%20new%20challenges%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20%26quot%3Blight%20fighter%26quot%3B%20concept%20was%20brought%20to%20the%20forefront%20of%20discussions%20about%20the%20future%20of%20American%20airpower%20by%20Air%20Force%20Chief%20of%20Staff%20Gen.%20David%20Allvin%20at%20the%20Global%20Air%20and%20Space%20Chiefs'%20Conference%20by%20the%20UK's%20Air%20and%20Space%20Power%20Association%20in%20London%20late%20in%20July%202024%20and%20was%20first%20brought%20to%20our%20attention%20by%20journalist%20Parth%20Satam%20at%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheaviationist.com%2F2024%2F08%2F19%2Flight-fighter-concept-ngad%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ET%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheaviationist.com%2F2024%2F08%2F19%2Flight-fighter-concept-ngad%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehe%20Aviationist%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20his%20presentation%2C%20Gen.%20Allvin%20proposed%20a%20significant%20shift%20in%20America's%20developmental%20approach%20to%20fielding%20new%20fighters%2C%20doing%20away%20with%20the%20long-standing%20%26quot%3Bbuilt%20to%20last%26quot%3B%20design%20approach%20that's%20predicated%20on%20fielding%20advanced%20and%20supremely%20expensive%20new%20fighters%20meant%20to%20operate%20for%20a%20half-century%20or%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20Allvin%20suggested%2C%20new%20fighter%20designs%20should%20be%20%26quot%3Bbuilt%20to%20adapt%2C%26quot%3B%20shifting%20focus%20away%20from%20long-term%20survivability%20and%20instead%20toward%20highly%20modular%20designs%20that%20can%20be%20quickly%20and%20easily%20modified%20to%20meet%20the%20ever-shifting%20challenges%20of%20the%2021st-century%20battlefield.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20Allvin%20did%20not%20mention%20the%20NGAD%20program%20in%20his%20remarks%2C%20these%20statements%20echo%20those%20made%20by%20others%20about%20the%20new%20air%20superiority%20fighter%20effort%20being%20placed%20in%20a%20strategic%20pause%20as%20the%20Air%20Force%20considers%20significant%20revisions%20to%20its%20design%20and%20operating%20model.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3Blight%20fighter%26quot%3B%20versus%20%26quot%3Bheavy%20fighter%26quot%3B%20nomenclature%20that's%20been%20attributed%20to%20Allvin's%20concept%20(he%20notably%20didn't%20use%20the%20terminology%20himself)%20is%20reminiscent%20of%20the%20Lightweight%20Fighter%20Program%20that%20produced%20the%20F-16%20as%20a%20low-cost%20wingman%20for%20the%20supremely%20expensive%20at%20the%20time%20F-15%20Eagle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20F-16's%20design%20focus%2C%20of%20course%2C%20was%20not%20on%20modularity%20or%20technological%20adaptability%20but%20was%20nonetheless%20groundbreaking%2C%20thanks%20to%20its%20emphasis%20on%20the%20energy-maneuverability%20theory%20of%20aerobatic%20performance%20and%20its%20first-of-its-kind%20adoption%20of%20fly-by-wire%20controls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22999%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22undercarriage%20an%20F-16%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b9fd5d7a3d271488760d23%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22714%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20undercarriage%20of%20an%20F-16%20mid-flight.%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20Force%20photo%20illustration%20by%20Staff%20Sgt.%20Madeline%20Herzog%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20while%20the%20F-16%20delivered%20important%20technological%20breakthroughs%2C%20its%20real%20claim%20to%20fame%20was%20the%20ability%20to%20fight%20well%20above%20its%20weight%20class%20for%20a%20serious%20bargain%20%E2%80%94%20ringing%20it%20at%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.upi.com%2FArchives%2F1985%2F07%2F09%2FPentagon-queries-jet-fighters-costs%2F1348489729600%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520actual%2520cost%2520of%2520an%2Cby%2520the%2520McDonnell%2520Douglas%2520Corp.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejust%20more%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20half%20the%20price%20of%20the%20heavy%20F-15%20per%20jet.%20This%20allowed%20the%20US%20Air%20Force%20to%20embrace%20what's%20commonly%20known%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bhigh%2Flow%20mix%26quot%3B%20of%20fighters%20%E2%80%94%20an%20approach%20that's%20transitioned%20over%20the%20years%20to%20see%20both%20the%20F-15%20and%20F-16%20as%20%26quot%3Blow%26quot%3B%20end%20fighters%2C%20with%20the%20F-22%20and%20F-35%20assuming%20the%20%26quot%3Bhigh%26quot%3B%20end%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllvin%20argued%20that%20America's%20existing%20approach%20to%20fighter%20design%2C%20which%20sees%20lengthy%20developmental%20timelines%20followed%20by%20high-cost%20procurements%20and%20even%20higher-cost%20sustainment%2C%20is%20predicated%20on%20the%20%26quot%3Bunderlying%20assumption%26quot%3B%20that%20the%20fighters%20will%20stay%20technologically%20relevant%20for%20long%20enough%20to%20substantiate%20the%20mountains%20of%20funding%20dollars%20the%20programs%20burn%20through.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20with%20a%20long%20list%20of%20foreign%20nations%20now%20fielding%20stealth%20fighters%20of%20their%20own%20and%20emerging%20technologies%20like%20artificial%20intelligence%20promising%20to%20make%20air%20defense%20systems%20more%20capable%20than%20ever%2C%20Allvin%20believes%20that%20%26quot%3Bunderlying%20assumption%26quot%3B%20no%20longer%20holds%20true.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20proposition%20can%20become%20an%20albatross.%20It's%20still%20functioning%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20as%20effective%2C%26quot%3B%20Allvin%20said%20of%20these%20high-end%20fighters%20as%20their%20lifespans%20wear%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2234e3605f-bb60-424b-b9d8-99c4168c30cb%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20%26quot%3Blight%20fighter%26quot%3B%20concept%20and%20the%20digital%20century%20series%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224928%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22F-35%20and%20F-22%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F546b5edf6da81199770e3d13%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223280%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20Force%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EInstead%20of%20repeating%20the%20lengthy%20development%20timelines%20of%20today's%20top-tier%20American%20fighters%20like%20the%20F-22%20and%20F-35%2C%20each%20of%20which%20stretched%20more%20than%20two%20decades%20between%20early%20developmental%20onset%20and%20reaching%20operational%20service%2C%20Allvin%20called%20for%20leaning%20further%20into%20open%20system%20software%20architecture%20and%20supremely%20modular%20designs%20that%20could%20be%20rapidly%20upgraded%20or%20even%20discarded%20in%20favor%20of%20newer%20designs%20that%20would%20share%20common%20systems%20with%20the%20previous%20model.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20a%20new%20concept%20for%20the%20US%20Air%20Force%2C%20and%20in%20fact%2C%20has%20been%20the%20subject%20of%20multiple%20discussions%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20both%20related%20and%20unrelated%20to%20the%20Next%20Generation%20Air%20Dominance%20fighter%20program%20that%20has%20been%20underway%2C%20in%20one%20form%20or%20another%2C%20for%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sandboxx.us%2Fnews%2Famericas-ngad-fighter-emerged-from-a-classified-billion-dollar-x-plane-program%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20solid%20decade%20already%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20many%20have%20dubbed%20Allvin's%20proposal%20a%20new%20%26quot%3Bnotional%20light%20fighter%20concept%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20very%20similar%20concept%20was%20proposed%20by%20Air%20Force%20acquisition%20chief%20Will%20Roper%20in%202019%20as%20what%20he%20called%20the%20%26quot%3Bdigital%20century%20series.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20title%2C%20of%20course%2C%20draws%20inspiration%20from%20the%20rapidly%20changing%20fighter%20designs%20of%20the%201950s%20collectively%20known%20as%20the%20%26quot%3BCentury%20Series%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20a%20half%20dozen%20fighters%20ranging%20from%20the%20North%20American%20F-100%20Super%20Sabre%20that%20entered%20service%20in%201954%20to%20the%20Convair%20F-106%20Delta%20Dart%20that%20followed%20suit%20in%201959.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20similar%20era%20of%20rapid%20advancements%20in%20aviation%20technology%2C%20the%20original%20Century%20series%20placed%20a%20significant%20emphasis%20on%20what%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rand.org%2Fcontent%2Fdam%2Frand%2Fpubs%2Fresearch_memoranda%2F2006%2FRM2549.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1960%20Rand%20Corporation%20analysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20described%20as%20an%20attempt%20%26quot%3Bto%20develop%20aircraft%20that%20embody%20state-in-the-art%20%5Bsic%5D%20advances%20and%20the%20flexibility%20with%20which%20aircraft%20subsystems%2C%20once%20developed%2C%20could%20be%20employed%20in%20systems%20for%20which%20they%20were%20not%20originally%20designed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20first%20four%20Century%20series%20fighters%3A%20F-100%2C%20F-101%2C%20F-102%2C%20and%20XF-104.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d74c2f289b805d1db3b164%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221012%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20first%20four%20Century%20series%20fighters%3A%20F-100%2C%20F-101%2C%20F-102%2C%20and%20XF-104.%3Cp%3ENational%20Museum%20of%20the%20US%20Air%20Force%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20the%20original%20Century%20Series%20of%20fighters%20aimed%20to%20make%20rapid%20technological%20progress%20through%20the%20use%20of%20somewhat%20modular%20avionics%20systems%20and%20other%20onboard%20equipment%20that%20could%20be%20reused%20in%20subsequent%20aircraft%20designs%20rather%20than%20needing%20to%20devise%20entirely%20new%20hardware%20for%20each.%20Roper's%20more%20modern%20%26quot%3BDigital%20Century%20Series%26quot%3B%20would%20take%20that%20concept%20to%20the%20next%20level%2C%20using%20digital%20engineering%20and%20virtual%20testing%20environments%20to%20rapidly%20mature%20fighter%20designs%20and%20subsystems%20toward%20service%20in%20modern%20modular%20fighters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGeneral%20Allvin%20also%20provided%20vocal%20support%20for%20Roper's%20pitch%20at%20the%20time%2C%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3B'Built%20to%20last'%20is%20a%20tremendous%2020th-century%20bumper%20sticker%2C%20and%20the%20assumption%20then%20was%2C%20whatever%20you%20had%20was%20relevant%20as%20long%20as%20it%20lasts.%20I'm%20not%20sure%20that's%20true%20anymore.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20a%20similar%20concept%20was%20also%20discussed%20by%20then-Air%20Force%20Chief%20of%20Staff%20(and%20current%20Chairman%20of%20the%20Joint%20Chiefs%20of%20Staff)%20General%20Charles%20%26quot%3BCQ%26quot%3B%20Brown%2C%20who%20suggested%20the%20branch%20shift%20toward%20fielding%20what%20many%20called%20a%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sandboxx.us%2Fnews%2Fthe-air-force-wants-a-new-fighter-to-fill-in-for-the-f-35%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E5th%20generation%20minus%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20fighter%20design%20that%20would%20leverage%20modular%20systems%20based%20on%20those%20developed%20for%20the%20F-22%20and%20F-35%20in%20lower-cost%20aircraft%20with%20shorter%20service%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20would%20allow%20for%20rapid%20advancements%20in%20aircraft%20design%20and%20performance%2C%20as%20each%20new%20fighter%20iteration%20would%20be%20similar%20to%20the%20last%2C%20with%20a%20series%20of%20improvements%20cultivated%20through%20experience%20with%20the%20previous%20design.%20Pilots%20and%20maintainers%20transitioning%20from%20one%20aircraft%20to%20the%20next%20would%20face%20minimal%20training%20challenges%2C%20as%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20systems%20and%20aircraft%20functionality%20would%20remain%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERather%20than%20fielding%20a%20new%20clean-sheet%20fighter%20design%20every%2010%20years%2C%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20previous%20fighter%20airframe%20and%20systems%20would%20be%20retained%20from%20one%20iteration%20to%20the%20next%2C%20swapping%20out%20only%20the%20design%20elements%20or%20internal%20components%20that%20need%20to%20be%20upgraded%20or%20changed%20to%20suit%20the%20shifting%20needs%20of%20the%20modern%20battlefield.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20iteration%20might%20come%20with%20a%20different%20wing%20or%20tail%20design%20meant%20to%20improve%20stealth%2C%20range%2C%20or%20loiter%20time%2C%20while%20the%20cockpit%2C%20avionics%2C%20and%20other%20onboard%20equipment%20could%20remain%20unchanged.%20Modular%20avionics%20systems%20could%20simply%20be%20swapped%20out%20of%20existing%20jets%20or%20replaced%20in%20the%20next%20iteration%2C%20resulting%20in%20a%20rotating%20fleet%20of%20fighters%20that%20are%20overwhelmingly%20similar%20to%20one%20another%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20training%20and%20maintenance%20but%20that%20continuously%20field%20new%20technologies%20or%20design%20methodologies%20meant%20to%20offset%20advancements%20in%20adversary%20defenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2206966796-8ed0-4964-afe4-8d0017940490%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBreathing%20new%20life%20into%20the%20fighter%20industry%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22860%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20F-22%20Raptors%20fly%20in%20formation%20with%20two%20Royal%20Norwegian%20Air%20Force%20F-35A%20Lightning%20II%20aircraft.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d74c8d1d8d2deb96b8463f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22394%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETwo%20F-22%20Raptors%20fly%20in%20formation%20with%20two%20Royal%20Norwegian%20Air%20Force%20F-35A%20Lightning%20II%20aircraft.%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20Force%20photo%20by%20Senior%20Airman%20Preston%20Cherry%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EShortening%20the%20intended%20service%20lives%20of%20fighters%20could%20potentially%20have%20even%20more%20benefits%20than%20ensuring%20the%20latest%20and%20greatest%20fighter%20tech%20is%20making%20it%20into%20the%20sky%3B%20it%20could%20also%20help%20to%20reinvigorate%20America's%20increasingly%20anemic%20fighter%20industry%20and%20dramatically%20reduce%20the%20most%20expensive%20part%20of%20any%20modern%20fighter%20program%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20long-term%20sustainment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20there%20are%20only%20three%20large%20American%20firms%20still%20in%20the%20fighter%20business%20%E2%80%94%20Lockheed%20Martin%2C%20Northrop%20Grumman%2C%20and%20Boeing%20%E2%80%94%20with%20little%20promise%20of%20any%20other%20company%20ever%20getting%20a%20foot%20in%20the%20door%20because%20new%20fighter%20programs%20are%20so%20few%20and%20far%20between.%20With%20Lockheed%20Martin%20securing%20contracts%20for%20both%20the%20F-22%20and%20F-35%2C%20it's%20been%20over%20four%20decades%20since%20the%20US%20fielded%20a%20completely%20new%20clean-sheet%20fighter%20design%20that%20didn't%20come%20from%20Lockheed's%20Skunk%20Works.%20With%20Lockheed%20Martin%20seen%20by%20many%20as%20the%20potential%20favorite%20for%20the%20Next%20Generation%20Air%20Dominance%20competition%2C%20it's%20entirely%20feasible%20that%20Lockheed%20Martin%20could%20maintain%20that%20new-fighter-design%20monopoly%20beyond%20the%20half-century%20mark%20or%20further.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20so%20few%20fighter%20contracts%20to%20go%20around%2C%20there's%20no%20opportunity%2C%20let%20alone%20incentive%2C%20for%20any%20other%20company%20to%20try%20throwing%20their%20hats%20into%20the%20fighter%20ring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20a%20shift%20toward%20fielding%20fighters%20only%20meant%20to%20serve%20for%20a%20decade%20or%20so%20would%20mean%20that%20initial%20development%20on%20the%20next%20fighter%20could%20begin%20as%20soon%20as%20the%20current%20one%20enters%20service.%20And%20by%20using%20open%20system%20software%20architecture%20meant%20to%20ensure%20components%20and%20systems%20developed%20by%20any%20company%20can%20integrate%20and%20work%20seamlessly%20with%20systems%20built%20by%20any%20other%2C%20each%20new%20fighter%20design%20would%20only%20need%20to%20swap%20out%20upgraded%20systems%20while%20retaining%20the%20old%20to%20keep%20costs%20down.%20This%20could%20even%20allow%20for%20smaller%20companies%20to%20submit%20their%20own%20modular%20designs%20using%20the%20same%20open%20framework.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20shortening%20a%20fighter's%20operational%20lifespan%20from%2060%2B%20years%20to%20around%2010%20to%2020%20might%20sound%20even%20pricier%20than%20funding%20exquisite%20jets%20like%20the%20F-35%2C%20there's%20a%20reasonable%20argument%20to%20be%20made%20that%20it%20would%20actually%20cost%20much%20less%20in%20the%20long%20run.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220c15fcca-e3e9-470b-b06a-4dd20f12e4e7%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECould%20building%20new%20fighters%20more%20often%20actually%20cost%20less%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22780%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22lockheed%20martin%20f-35%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F585de63bf10a9a23008b53dd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22518%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20US%20Marine%20Corps%20Lockheed%20Martin%20F-35B%20fighter%20jet%20taxis%20after%20landing%20at%20the%20Royal%20International%20Air%20Tattoo%20at%20Fairford%2C%20Britain%20July%208%2C%202016.%3Cp%3EReuters%2FPeter%20Nicholls%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EToday%2C%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20a%20fighter's%20overall%20program%20cost%20is%20associated%20with%20long-tail%20sustainment%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20the%20cost%20of%20operating%2C%20maintaining%2C%20repairing%2C%20and%20upgrading%20aircraft%20over%20their%20intended%20lifespans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20F-35%20program%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20is%20often%20referred%20to%20as%20a%20%242%20trillion%20effort%20as%20though%20that%20immense%20figure%20represents%20the%20high%20research%2C%20development%2C%20and%20procurement%20costs%20of%20these%20jets%20when%2C%20in%20reality%2C%20%241.6%20trillion%20of%20that%20figure%20%E2%80%94%20a%20whopping%2080%25%20of%20the%20total%20cost%20%E2%80%94%20comes%20from%20the%20projected%20maintenance%20and%20sustainment%20required%20to%20keep%20the%20stealth%20fighter%20viable%20throughout%20its%20intended%20lifespan%2C%20which%20stretches%20all%20the%20way%20into%20the%202080s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20dramatically%20oversimplify%20the%20math%2C%20that%20shakes%20out%20to%20about%20%242%20trillion%20for%20a%20fleet%20of%20roughly%202%2C500%20fighters%20operated%20over%20the%20span%20of%2065%20or%20so%20years%20%E2%80%94%20or%20roughly%20%24800%20million%20invested%20into%20each%20airframe%20for%20six%20and%20a%20half%20decades%20of%20service%2C%20with%20around%20%24640%20million%20dedicated%20to%20sustainment%20and%20only%20around%20%24160%20million%20in%20research%2C%20development%2C%20and%20procurement%20costs%20per%20jet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20new%20Lockheed%20Martin%20F-35A%20Lightning%20ll%20multirole%20fighter%20jet%20parked%20in%20a%20hangar%20as%20it%20is%20presented%20to%20media%20at%20the%20Lockheed%20Martin%20factory%20in%20Fort%20Worth.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667acda9d1c84a0eaca77e35%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20new%20Lockheed%20Martin%20F-35A%20Lightning%20ll%20multirole%20fighter%20jet%20parked%20in%20a%20hangar%20as%20it%20is%20presented%20to%20media%20at%20the%20Lockheed%20Martin%20factory%20in%20Fort%20Worth.%3Cp%3EOrjan%20F.%20Ellingvag%2FCorbis%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20sustainment%20costs%20tend%20to%20increase%20over%20time%20(just%20like%20it%20costs%20more%20to%20keep%20an%20old%20car%20on%20the%20road)%2C%20if%20we%20simplify%20the%20math%20by%20averaging%20the%20F-35's%20projected%20expenses%20over%20that%20lifespan%2C%20sustainment%20costs%20alone%20could%20fund%20the%20research%2C%20development%2C%20and%20procurement%20of%20a%20new%20comparable%20fighter%20design%20every%2016.25%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20when%20you%20consider%20the%20use%20of%20modular%20systems%20already%20in%20production%20for%20each%20subsequent%20design%20and%20eliminating%20the%20need%20for%20building%20airframe-specific%20repair%20depots%20and%20the%20like%2C%20it%20starts%20to%20look%20pretty%20feasible%20that%20fielding%20new%20fighters%20every%2010%20to%2015%20years%20could%20even%20be%20the%20lower%20cost%20option.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20that%20possibility%20does%20come%20with%20a%20fairly%20sizable%20list%20of%20assumptions%2C%20including%20the%20idea%20that%20repair%20depots%20for%20integral%20components%20wouldn't%20require%20significant%20overhauls%20between%20fighter%20iterations%20and%20that%20emerging%20technologies%20would%20continue%20to%20more-or-less%20mirror%20the%20repeated%20cost%20overruns%20of%20the%20F-35%20program%2C%20so%20the%20actual%20cost%20of%20transitioning%20to%20this%20more%20frequent%20acquisition%20model%20could%20feasibly%20end%20up%20significantly%20higher%20or%20lower%20than%20our%20estimates%20%E2%80%94%20and%20there's%20the%20rub.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22976ba193-6481-4230-9289-7b24fffcd34f%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EEmbracing%20adaptability%20means%20embracing%20uncertainty%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20final%20F-22%20Raptor%20fighter%20jet%20to%20be%20produced%20for%20the%20Air%20Force%20is%20on%20display.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d74d4714a5cd1fcc8cc490%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22663%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20final%20F-22%20Raptor%20fighter%20jet%20to%20be%20produced%20for%20the%20Air%20Force%20is%20on%20display.%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20Force%20photo%2FSenior%20Airman%20Danielle%20Purnell%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EThe%20biggest%20problem%20with%20shifting%20to%20the%20Light%20Fighter%20or%20Digital%20Century%20Series%20acquisition%20model%20for%20the%20US%20Air%20Force%20is%20that%20it's%20simply%20never%20been%20attempted%20in%20the%20modern%20era%2C%20and%20as%20such%2C%20there%20are%20few%20places%20to%20look%20for%20reliable%20data%20when%20attempting%20to%20assess%20the%20most%20effective%20path%20forward.%20Either%20decision%20will%20quickly%20become%20the%20fulcrum%20point%20of%20a%20new%20cost%20lever%20that%20stretches%20all%20the%20way%20to%20the%20end%20of%20the%2021st%20century%2C%20and%20as%20such%2C%20a%20seemingly%20small%20miscalculation%20on%20today's%20end%20could%20very%20quickly%20become%20an%20insurmountable%20budgetary%20shortfall%20a%20few%20decades%20down%20the%20road.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAir%20Force%20acquisitions%20are%20an%20industrial%20and%20economic%20behemoth%2C%20and%20as%20is%20the%20case%20with%20any%20massive%20enterprise%2C%20making%20such%20a%20dramatic%20pivot%20would%20require%20overcoming%20a%20great%20deal%20of%20cultural%20inertia%20both%20within%20the%20branch%20and%2C%20even%20more%20likely%2C%20within%20America's%20industrial%20base.%20For%20companies%20like%20Lockheed%20Martin%2C%20winning%20a%20fighter%20contract%20that%20includes%20long-term%20sustainment%20is%20effectively%20a%20guarantee%20of%20massive%20revenue%20numbers%20for%20a%20half-century%20or%20more%2C%20and%20that's%20something%20these%20influential%20corporate%20giants%20would%20likely%20fight%20to%20keep%20on%20Capitol%20Hill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20isn't%20to%20say%20these%20aren't%20challenges%20that%20can%20be%20overcome%20%E2%80%94%20airpower%20has%20always%20been%20an%20evolving%20enterprise%2C%20after%20all%20%E2%80%94%20but%20with%20so%20many%20question%20marks%20looming%20overhead%20and%20the%20near%20certainty%20that%20such%20a%20shift%20would%20face%20some%20serious%20political%20challenges%2C%20one%20could%20make%20a%20reasonable%20argument%20that%20it's%20simply%20too%20late%20to%20try%20to%20force%20this%20change%20onto%20the%20fighters%20already%20in%20development%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20these%20new%20jets%20into%20service%20under%20an%20all-new%20acquisition%20model%20within%20strategically%20necessary%20timelines%20would%20require%20immediately%20implementing%20these%20sweeping%20changes%20across%20the%20branch%2C%20the%20industry%20base%2C%20the%20designs%20themselves%2C%20and%20the%20Air%20Force%20training%20doctrine%20all%20at%20once%20%E2%80%94%20all%20while%20the%20Air%20Force%20splits%20its%20budget%20and%20focus%20among%20other%20high-profile%20endeavors%20already%20underway%20like%20the%20B-21%20Raider%20and%20LGM-35A%20Sentinel%20ICBM.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20to%20be%20clear%2C%20that's%20not%20just%20the%20assessment%20of%20a%20cynical%20researcher%20looking%20for%20holes%20to%20poke%20in%20an%20exciting%20new%20concept%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20actually%20the%20position%20argued%20by%20Air%20Force%20Secretary%20Frank%20Kendall%20just%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Air%20Force%20Secretary%20Frank%20Kendall%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66166d5816bde8d4ead73e43%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAir%20Force%20Secretary%20Frank%20Kendall.%3Cp%3ETom%20Williams%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20directly%20about%20how%20the%20transition%20to%20digital%20engineering%20and%20virtual%20testing%20environments%20could%20allow%20for%20Will%20Roper's%20proposed%20Digital%20Century%20Series%20approach%20to%20fighter%20acquisitions%2C%20Kendall%20%E2%80%94%20who%20is%20seen%20as%20the%20mastermind%20behind%20the%20Air%20Force's%20ongoing%20efforts%20to%20field%20AI-enabled%20drone%20wingmen%20being%20designed%20using%20a%20similar%20approach%20%E2%80%94%20tried%20to%20reign%20in%20the%20growing%20enthusiasm%20for%20the%20idea%2C%20even%20going%20so%20far%20as%20to%20call%20it%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.twz.com%2Fair-force-boss-gives-reality-check-on-over-hyped-digital-engineering-revolution%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoverhyped%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20respect%20for%20Will%20Roper.%20I've%20worked%20with%20him%20a%20lot%2C%26quot%3B%20Kendall%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.twz.com%2Faffordable-mass-concept-driving-air-forces-new-advanced-drone-initiative%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20he%20has%20some%20really%20interesting%20ideas%20%E2%80%A6%20%5Bbut%5D%20I%20think%20you%20have%20to%20be%20careful%20about%20where%20you%20apply%20those%20ideas.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Kendall%2C%20digital%20engineering%20and%20increasing%20modularity%20throughout%20fighter%20designs%20could%20have%20a%20massive%20impact%20on%20both%20developmental%20costs%20and%20timelines%2C%20but%20realistically%2C%20might%20reduce%20each%20by%20around%20(a%20still%20notable)%2020%25%2C%20rather%20than%20ushering%20in%20a%20revolution%20in%20aircraft%20acquisitions.%20Kendall%20also%20clarified%20that%20he%20isn't%20entirely%20confident%20in%20even%20that%2020%25%20figure%20because%2C%20again%2C%20there's%20simply%20no%20good%20data%20to%20look%20to%20for%20modeling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%2C%20as%20General%20Allvin%20recently%20pointed%20out%2C%20Northrop%20Grumman's%20B-21%20Raider%20stealth%20bomber%20and%20Lockheed%20Martin's%20new%20Mako%20hypersonic%20missile%20%E2%80%94%20both%20designed%20and%20tested%20in%20digital%20environments%20%E2%80%94%20could%20each%20become%20models%20for%20programs%20of%20the%20future%20to%20emulate%20(and%20for%20future%20predictive%20modeling).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Kendall%20also%20pointed%20out%20how%20similar%20claims%20about%20digital%20engineering%20were%20made%20during%20the%20F-35's%20development%20cycle%2C%20which%20clearly%20didn't%20manifest%20as%20predicted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDigital%20engineering%20isn't%20magic%2C%26quot%3B%20Even%20Roper%20agreed.%20%26quot%3BJust%20because%20you%20use%20it%20doesn't%20mean%20that%20all%20the%20problems%20of%20acquisition%20get%20out%20of%20your%20way.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2231b47329-f2e2-4625-80c9-8c749220f460%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Air%20Force%20needs%20new%20missiles%2C%20new%20bombers%2C%20and%20new%20fighters%20%E2%80%94%20but%20is%20struggling%20to%20pay%20for%20them%20all%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20B-21%20Raider%20in%20flight%20at%20Edwards%20Air%20Force%20Base%2C%20California.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d74dbb289b805d1db3b2c4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221668%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20B-21%20Raider%20in%20flight%20at%20Edwards%20Air%20Force%20Base%2C%20California.%3Cp%3ENorthrop%20Grumman%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ELast%20year%2C%20it%20seemed%20as%20though%20Kendall%20had%20nixed%20the%20idea%20of%20pursuing%20this%20concept%20for%20at%20least%20the%20time%20being%2C%20but%20since%20then%2C%20the%20Air%20Force's%20economic%20outlook%20for%20the%20years%20ahead%20has%20certainly%20changed%20%E2%80%94%20so%20much%20so%20that%20the%20Next%20Generation%20Air%20Dominance%20fighter%20program%20that%20was%20expected%20to%20deliver%20a%20production%20contract%20this%20year%20is%20now%20being%20re-evaluated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20too-important-to-fail%20programs%20like%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sandboxx.us%2Fnews%2Feverything-you-need-to-know-about-americas-struggle-to-replace-its-aging-icbm-arsenal%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELGM-35A%20Sentinel%20ICBM%20swell%20to%2081%20percent%20over%20budget%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Air%20Force%20has%20to%20adjust%20to%20accommodate%20the%20loss%20of%20tens%20of%20billions%20of%20dollars%20in%20near-future%20planning%2C%20and%20with%20contracts%20already%20awarded%20for%20these%20new%20missiles%20and%20new%20stealth%20bombers%20in%20the%20B-21%20Raider%2C%20the%20only%20big-ticket%20item%20left%20on%20the%20chopping%20block%20is%20America's%20next%20air%20superiority%20fighter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMultiple%20different%20options%20are%20now%20being%20considered%20to%20ensure%20America%20can%20maintain%20air%20dominance%20in%20the%20decades%20ahead%2C%20but%20for%20significantly%20less%20than%20initially%20anticipated.%20This%20includes%20stretching%20the%20service%20lives%20of%20F-22%20Raptors%2C%20which%20are%20already%20amid%20a%20multibillion-dollar%20update%20meant%20to%20ensure%20they%20overmatch%20the%20most%20advance