re's%20the%20light%20fighter%20concept%20that%20places%20a%20new%20emphasis%20on%20adaptability%20over%20longevity%20%E2%80%94%20which%20would%20see%20the%20United%20States%20field%20fighters%20meant%20not%20to%20fly%20for%206%2C000%2C%208%2C000%2C%20or%20even%2020%2C000%20hours%20like%20the%20F-15EX%2C%20but%20instead%20for%20less%20than%204%2C000%20%E2%80%94%20with%20design%20for%20replacements%20already%20underway%20when%20each%20new%20fighter%20enters%20operational%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20model%20has%20tons%20of%20potential%20to%20help%20ensure%20America%20fields%20only%20the%20latest%20and%20most%20capable%20tactical%20aircraft%20in%20the%20world.%20It's%20an%20approach%20to%20aircraft%20design%20that%20could%20change%20everything%20about%20air%20warfare%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20also%20comes%20with%20arguably%20even%20larger%20risks%20than%20today's%20long-standing%20acquisition%20model.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20today's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sandboxx.us%2Fnews%2Famericas-ngad-fighter-isnt-dead-but-it-is-changing%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENGAD%20woes%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20be%20traced%2C%20at%20least%20in%20some%20part%2C%20to%20overages%20associated%20with%20America's%20new%20ICBM%2C%20we%20need%20to%20look%20no%20further%20than%20its%20current%20ICBM%20fleet%20to%20see%20the%20dangers%20associated%20with%20assuming%20defense%20budgets%20will%20allow%20for%20replacement%20systems%20to%20actually%20come%20online%20every%2010%20or%20so%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2265e73f0d-3474-48f2-81d0-204afe0f8943%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBuilding%20the%20'Minuteman%20III'%20of%20fighters%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221423%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20plume%20of%20smoke%20surrounds%20the%20last%20unarmed%20Minuteman%20III%20during%20launch.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d74e251d8d2deb96b8478d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221049%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20plume%20of%20smoke%20surrounds%20the%20last%20unarmed%20Minuteman%20III%20during%20launch.%3Cp%3EAFNWC%20History%20Office%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EThe%20LGM-30G%20Minuteman%20III%20ICBMs%20America%20operates%20as%20its%20land-based%20nuclear%20deterrent%20today%20started%20entering%20service%20all%20the%20way%20back%20in%201970%20with%20a%20projected%2010-year%20service%20life%2C%20meaning%20they%20were%20slated%20to%20be%20replaced%20by%20newer%20and%20more%20modern%20weapons%20starting%20in%201980.%20Its%20intended%20replacement%2C%20eventually%20known%20as%20the%20LGM-118A%20Peacekeeper%2C%20didn't%20make%20its%20first%20test%20flight%20until%201983%2C%20with%20the%20first%2010%20weapons%20reaching%20service%20in%201986.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20shifting%20geopolitical%20landscape%20following%20the%20fall%20of%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20in%201991%20and%20the%20subsequent%20Strategic%20Arms%20Reduction%20Treaty%20(START)%20II%20signed%20in%201993%20saw%20only%2050%20Peacekeepers%20ever%20built%20%E2%80%94%20all%20of%20which%20were%20subsequently%20retired%20by%202005.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20the%20United%20States%20has%20spent%20billions%20trying%20to%20keep%20its%20aging%20Minuteman%20IIIs%20viable%20decades%20after%20their%20intended%20lifespans%20and%20now%20has%20acknowledged%20that%20they've%20reached%20the%20point%20where%20it's%20no%20longer%20feasible%20to%20keep%20them%20in%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20the%20Air%20Force%20now%20has%20no%20choice%20but%20to%20swallow%20the%20ballooning%20cost%20of%20this%20program%2C%20which%20has%20nearly%20doubled%20in%20budget%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20simply%20because%20the%20missiles%20that%20were%20initially%20meant%20to%20serve%20for%20roughly%2010%20years%20will%20now%20be%20on%20duty%20beyond%20their%2060th%20birthday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221331%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20sergeant%20inspects%20a%20Minuteman%20III%20ICBM.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b0abf5a5247369a3e96cc7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Minuteman%20III%2C%20the%20US%20intercontinental%20ballistic%20missile%2C%20hearkens%20back%20to%20the%20Cold%20War%20and%20is%20being%20replaced%20by%20the%20modern%20Sentinel%20missile.%3Cp%3EUSAF%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20missiles%20and%20fighters%20are%20certainly%20not%20the%20same%20types%20of%20programs%2C%20the%20lack%20of%20data%20we%20have%20to%20pull%20from%20to%20inform%20a%20decision%20about%20short-lifespan%20fighters%20leaves%20us%20with%20few%20places%20to%20look%20outside%20the%20confines%20of%20Air%20Force%20acquisitions%20in%20recent%20decades%20%E2%80%94%20which%20are%2C%20of%20course%2C%20informed%20by%20the%20contemporary%20politics%20surrounding%20these%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fact%20of%20the%20matter%20is%20that%20awarding%20a%20production%20contract%20for%20any%20fighter%20(or%20really%2C%20any%20military%20platform%2C%20for%20that%20matter)%20is%20%E2%80%94%20to%20some%20extent%20%E2%80%94%20a%20gamble.%20The%20Pentagon%20may%20know%20how%20well%20the%20prototypes%20and%20technology%20demonstrators%20perform%2C%20but%20it's%20betting%20on%20the%20winning%20firm%20to%20be%20able%20to%20mass%20produce%20the%20same%20capabilities%20for%20a%20projected%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20betting%20that%20there%20won't%20be%20any%20significant%20unforeseen%20technical%20challenges%20once%20the%20platforms%20reach%20the%20field%2C%20betting%20on%20continued%20Defense%20priorities%20throughout%20the%20production%20run%2C%20and%20%E2%80%94%20maybe%20the%20biggest%20gamble%20of%20all%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20betting%20on%20continued%20political%20support%20for%20years%20or%20even%20decades%20as%20a%20design%20on%20a%20sheet%20of%20paper%20matures%20into%20an%20operational%20fleet%20of%20platforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20the%20idea%20of%20rapidly%20adaptable%20fighter%20designs%20meant%20to%20be%20thrown%20away%20every%2010%20years%20does%20sound%20incredibly%20promising%2C%20actually%20executing%20such%20a%20dramatic%20shift%20in%20acquisition%20will%20require%20an%20immense%20amount%20of%20political%20and%20industrial%20buy-in%20%E2%80%94%20something%20that%20won't%20come%20easily%20without%20a%20clear%20upside%20for%20both%20parties.%20But%20even%20if%20that%20can%20be%20accomplished%20quickly%20enough%20to%20field%20a%20new%20air%20superiority%20fighter%20in%20the%20early%202030s%2C%20when%20even%20upgraded%20F-22s%20will%20be%20starting%20to%20get%20pretty%20long%20in%20the%20tooth%2C%20that%20wouldn't%20be%20the%20end%20of%20the%20challenge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20F-22%20production%20line%20at%20Lockheed%20Martin%20Aeronautics%20Company%20in%20Marietta%2C%20Georgia.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d74f1c1d8d2deb96b849b2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22415%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20F-22%20production%20line%20at%20Lockheed%20Martin%20Aeronautics%20Company%20in%20Marietta%2C%20Georgia.%3Cp%3ELockheed%20Martin%2FFlickr%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Air%20Force%20would%20almost%20invariably%20find%20itself%20having%20to%20argue%20to%20justify%20the%20purchase%20of%20a%20new%20slew%20of%20fighters%20in%20the%202040s%2C%20as%20lawmakers%20question%20whether%20the%20jets%20designed%20to%20last%20for%20only%20one%20decade%20really%20need%20to%20be%20replaced%20after%20all%2C%20with%20many%20arguing%20that%20swapping%20out%20modular%20systems%20should%20be%20sufficient%20to%20maintain%20its%20competitive%20edge.%20Then%2C%20the%20debate%20would%20begin%20anew%20in%20the%202050s%2C%20the%202060s%2C%20and%20so%20on%2C%20with%20the%20concept's%20efficacy%20teetering%20in%20the%20balance%20every%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20the%20Minuteman%20III%2C%20which%20was%20originally%20slated%20for%20just%20a%2010-year%20service%20life%2C%20the%20LGM-35A%20Sentinel%20is%20expected%20to%20stay%20in%20service%20for%20better%20than%20a%20half-century%20because%20the%20Air%20Force%20has%20no%20intention%20of%20making%20the%20same%20mistake%20twice%20with%20these%20long-range%20munitions.%20It's%20well%20aware%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20fielding%20ICBMs%20that%20would%20need%20replacements%2010%20years%20down%20the%20road%20assumes%20funding%20for%20those%20replacements%20will%20be%20forthcoming%2C%20and%20in%20today's%20political%20climate%2C%20that's%20an%20awfully%20big%20assumption.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20yet%2C%20because%20of%20the%20Sentinel's%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sandboxx.us%2Fnews%2Feverything-you-need-to-know-about-americas-struggle-to-replace-its-aging-icbm-arsenal%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimmense%20cost%20overruns%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20NGAD%20program%20now%20runs%20the%20risk%20of%20becoming%20the%20fighter%20equivalent%20of%20the%20Minuteman%20III%20itself%20%E2%80%94%20a%20system%20meant%20to%20serve%20for%2010%20years%20but%20dragged%20down%20the%20road%20for%20decades%20as%20officials%20and%20lawmakers%20try%20to%20dodge%20the%20sticker-shock%20of%20fielding%20a%20replacement%20until%20they%20have%20no%20other%20options%20left.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%2C%20when%20that%20program%20goes%2081%25%20over%20budget%20before%20the%20first%20aircraft%20is%20even%20delivered%20the%20way%20Sentinel%20has%2C%20Defense%20officials%20would%20be%20forced%20to%20echo%20the%20same%20talking%20points%20about%20how%20the%20strategic%20need%20for%20replacement%20outweighs%20the%20economic%20impact%20of%20cost%20overruns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227d65e52d-fb36-4d9d-a415-e8e1ad7aa1d9%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECultural%20inertia%20in%20the%20fighter%20business%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A-10%2C%20two%20F-15s%2C%20an%20F-16%2C%20and%20an%20F-22%20%20fly%20in%20formation.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d75034289b805d1db3b53f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22912%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20Air%20Force%20fighter%20aircraft%20fly%20in%20formation.%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20Force%20photo%20by%20Tech.%20Sgt.%20John%20Raven%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ESo%2C%20does%20this%20idea%20of%20fielding%20lower-cost%20fighters%20more%20frequently%20make%20sense%3F%20In%20a%20lot%20of%20ways%2C%20it%20definitely%20does%2C%20and%20to%20be%20clear%2C%20this%20is%20very%20much%20the%20design%20methodology%20being%20employed%20for%20a%20variety%20of%20unmanned%20platforms%20like%20the%20collaborative%20combat%20aircraft%20(CCAs)%20currently%20making%20their%20way%20toward%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20big-ticket%20acquisitions%20like%20fighters%2C%20bombers%2C%20and%20warships%20are%20subject%20to%20far%20more%20than%20military%20considerations%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20the%20subject%20of%20immense%20public%20scrutiny%20and%20lawmaker%20debate%20that%20can%20span%20decades%2C%20and%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20court%20of%20public%20opinion%2C%20there%20are%20no%20guarantees%20that%20extend%20beyond%20the%20end%20of%20the%20week%2C%20let%20alone%20the%20end%20of%20the%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20impossible%20that%20such%20a%20concept%20could%20work%2C%20and%20if%20Uncle%20Sam%20could%20pull%20it%20off%2C%20it%20might%20make%20for%20the%20most%20incredible%20series%20of%20tactical%20aircraft%20this%20world%20has%20ever%20seen%E2%80%A6%20But%20in%20today's%20political%20world%2C%20it%20seems%20like%20a%20miracle%20when%20lawmakers%20can%20come%20together%20and%20agree%20to%20fund%20a%20tent-pole%20program%20like%20air%20superiority%20fighters%E2%80%A6%20And%20it%20seems%20dangerous%20to%20bet%20on%20that%20miracle%20happening%20on%20schedule%2C%20over%20and%20over%20again%2C%20as%20each%20tranche%20of%20new%20fighters%20begins%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20optimal%20solution%20might%20truly%20be%20found%20in%20the%20lineage%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Blight%20fighter%26quot%3B%20terminology%20itself%2C%20which%20was%20famously%20attributed%20to%20the%20F-16%20program%20as%20a%20means%20to%20provide%20America'%20with%20sufficient%20fighter%20capacity%20when%20it%20became%20clear%20the%20Air%20Force%20couldn't%20afford%20to%20procure%20F-15s%20in%20sufficient%20numbers%20to%20meet%20the%20force's%20strategic%20needs.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20the%20Lightweight%20Fighter%20Program's%20success%20with%20the%20F-16%20didn't%20see%20the%20cancellation%20of%20the%20F-15%20it%20was%20meant%20to%20supplement%20%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20new%20%26quot%3Blightweight%20fighter%26quot%3B%20meant%20to%20supplement%20the%20NGAD%20program%20could%20provide%20similar%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20possibility%20was%20even%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.airandspaceforces.com%2Fngad-multirole-fighter-f-35-block-4%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehinted%20at%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20retired%20Gen.%20James%20M.%20Holmes%2C%20former%20head%20of%20the%20Air%20Force's%20Air%20Combat%20Command%20in%202021%2C%20when%20he%20said%20the%20branch%20may%20ultimately%20field%20two%20variants%20of%20the%20fighter%20to%20emerge%20from%20the%20NGAD%20program%20%E2%80%94%20one%20with%20more%20range%20and%20payload%20capacity%20for%20extended%20engagements%20over%20the%20Pacific%20(which%20would%20be%20the%20pricier%20of%20the%20two)%2C%20and%20a%20separate%2C%20smaller%20(i.e.%20lighter)%20design%20meant%20for%20shorter-ranged%20operations%20in%20places%20like%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20rendering%20of%20a%20future%20crewed%20next-generation%20air%20dominance%20aircraft%20by%20the%20US%20Air%20Force%20Research%20Laboratory.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d758101d8d2deb96b8566c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20rendering%20of%20a%20future%20crewed%20next-generation%20air%20dominance%20aircraft%20by%20the%20US%20Air%20Force%20Research%20Laboratory.%3Cp%3ERTX%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20use%20of%20modular%20systems%20and%20open%20system%20software%20architecture%20would%20allow%20for%20a%20great%20deal%20of%20commonality%20between%20airframes%2C%20reducing%20the%20costs%20associated%20with%20standing%20up%20two%20separate%20fighter%20production%20lines.%20Nonetheless%2C%20for%20a%20cash-strapped%20Air%20Force%2C%20this%20would%20be%20a%20significant%20challenge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20of%20course%2C%20with%20the%20F-35%20still%20in%20active%20production%2C%20the%20arithmetic%20gets%20even%20more%20complicated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20might%20reasonably%20argue%20that%20the%20F-35%20itself%2C%20which%20now%20rings%20in%20at%20an%20average%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbreakingdefense.com%2F2023%2F10%2Fnewest-f-35-f-15ex-contracts-are-set-but-how-much-do-they-cost-exclusive%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2482.5%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20per%20runway%20variant%20%E2%80%94%20roughly%20%247.5%20million%20less%20than%20a%20new%20F-15EX%20%E2%80%94%20is%20already%20positioned%20to%20fill%20that%20%26quot%3Blow%26quot%3B%20end%20role%20as%20compared%20to%20the%20NGAD's%20anticipated%20flyaway%20costs%20of%20some%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sandboxx.us%2Fnews%2Fairpower%2Fwhy-americas-new-ngad-fighter-could-be-a-bargain-even-at-300-million-each%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%24300%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20per%20airframe.%20After%20all%2C%20%2482.5%20million%20may%20sound%20like%20a%20lot%2C%20but%20it's%20significantly%20lower%20than%20the%20adjusted%20prices%20on%20some%20of%20the%20previous%20era's%20top-tier%20platforms%20like%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F1975%2F09%2F16%2Farchives%2Fgrumman-confirms-rise-in-price-of-f14-fighters.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EF-14%20Tomcat%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%2C%20when%20adjusted%20to%20today's%20inflation%2C%20cost%20nearly%20%24121%20million%20per%20unit%20in%20the%201970s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20then%2C%20in%20my%20lifetime%2C%20we've%20seen%20things%20like%20stealth%20go%20from%20a%20handful%20of%20boutique%2C%20specialized%2C%20and%20classified%20airframes%20that%20operated%20in%20secret%20and%20only%20under%20cover%20of%20darkness%20to%20the%20F-35%20becoming%20one%20of%20the%20most%20widely%20operated%20fighters%20on%20the%20planet%2C%20with%20more%20than%201%2C000%20airframes%20delivered%20and%20production%20expected%20to%20continue%20well%20into%20the%202040s%20to%20meet%20demand.%20There%20is%20simply%20no%20denying%20that%20things%20are%20changing%20%E2%80%94%20and%20changing%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20maybe%20I'm%20just%20being%20a%20part%20of%20that%20cultural%20inertia%20that%20such%20a%20momentous%20plan%20would%20need%20to%20overcome%20in%20order%20to%20succeed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERead%20more%20from%20Sandboxx%20News%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sandboxx.us%2Fnews%2Fukrainian-f-16-jets-will-have-the-same-problem-its-abrams-tanks-had-says-zelenskyy%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUkrainian%20F-16%20jets%20will%20have%20the%20same%20problem%20its%20Abrams%20tanks%20had%2C%20says%20Zelenskyy%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sandboxx.us%2Fnews%2Fthese-are-the-us-aircraft-qualified-to-carry-nuclear-weapons%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThese%20are%20